<subSubSection id="2FB054F6B05FFFCA0EEEFF16A495FEBE" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="6715077DB05FFFCA0EEEFF16A495FEBE" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB05FFFCA0EEEFF16A15BFF22" bold="true" box="[199,295,223,248]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Biology.</emphasis>
Very rare species of sandy wetlands, in most countries endangered or extinct. The distribution is much weaker than in the past. The host is 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB05FFFCA0C00FECDA355FEC6" box="[553,809,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zonulum">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB05FFFCA0C00FECDA355FEC6" box="[553,809,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lasioglossum zonulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, recorded in the literature (
<bibRefCitation id="033B7A8CB05FFFCA0A73FECDA578FEC6" author="Bluthgen" box="[1114,1284,260,284]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Bluthgen, P. (1934) Die Wirte der Palaarktischen Sphecodes - Arten. Zeitschrift Wissenschaftlicher Insekten-Biologie, 27, 33 - 42, 61 - 66. Bluthgen, P. (1935) Halictus, Nomioides und Sphecodes, pp. 360 - 367. In: Popov, V. V. (ed.) Beitrage zur Bienenfauna von Tadzhikistan. Trudy Tajikskoy Bazy Akademie Nauk SSSR, 5, 1 - 408." type="book chapter" year="1934">
BlÃ¼thgen 
<number id="D162155AB05FFFCA0AE0FECDA578FEC6" box="[1225,1284,260,284]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1934.0">1934</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, Yates 
<number id="D162155AB05FFFCA0B7AFECDA5F3FEC6" box="[1363,1423,260,284]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2002.0">2002</number>
), the first author also recorded 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB05FFFCA0FC3FEE1A2A8FE9A" box="[490,724,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compressus">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB05FFFCA0FC3FEE1A2A8FE9A" box="[490,724,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Halictus compressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB05FFFCA0CCDFEE0A3DEFE9A" box="[740,930,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadricinctus">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB05FFFCA0CCDFEE0A3DEFE9A" box="[740,930,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. quadricinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB05FFFCA0DF5FEE1A495FE9A" box="[988,1257,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasinum">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB05FFFCA0DF5FEE1A495FE9A" box="[988,1257,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lasioglossum prasinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as likely hosts. More recently, parasitation only in nests of 
<taxonomicName id="A0AA7CFEB05FFFCA0C54FE84A286FEBE" box="[637,762,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zonulum">
<emphasis id="55DEDB6FB05FFFCA0C54FE84A286FEBE" box="[637,762,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">L. zonulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed (M. Herrmann, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
